         <div>
            <head>15.6.1882 Donnerstag</head>
            <p>
               <placeName type="write" key="49097">Ascot</placeName> June 15. 1882. Thursday.</p>
            <p> Sis&#x2019; funeral took place. The order of the procession was as follows: first came the
               hearse, (the hearse was a whealbarrow on which was placed a hutch on top of the hutch
               was placed the coffin, both hutch and coffin being entirely covered by a large black
               shawl, strewn with white pinks), with <persName key="763">Schuster</persName> tolling
               the bell on one side of it and <persName key="916">Jay</persName> carrying the spade
               on the other; next came the two mourning coaches with rabbits inside, next came I
               vainly smelling an onion, and last of all <persName key="667">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">r</hi>
                  </hi>
               </persName> and <persName key="760">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">rs</hi>
                  </hi> Kynnersley</persName>, <persName key="939">M<hi rend="ul.2">
                     <hi rend="sup">rs</hi>
                  </hi> Macdonald</persName> and <persName key="1139">Miss Macdonald</persName>. We
               went the most round about way we could, the little rabbits enjoying themselves
               prodigiously and munching away at some ferns all the time then &#x201e;Sis&#x201c; was let into the
               family vault: but at that moment the smell was so overpowering that the coffin was
               quickly let down, tilted over and covered with earth. A square headstone has been
               ordered with the inscription: HERE LIES &#x201e;SIS&#x201c; A FAITHFUL RABBIT. BORN APRIL 3 1878,
               DIED JUNE 14 1882.</p>
